### Analysis of the Main Target Image:

- **Count & Layers:** The structure consists of 7 building blocks arranged in a vertical stack with three distinct layers.
- **Spatial Relationships:**
  - The bottom layer has a red block with a circular cutout, supported by two yellow rectangular blocks on either side.
  - The middle layer features a green rectangular block standing vertically, flanked by two yellow horizontal bars.
  - The top layer includes an orange triangular block placed centrally on top of the green block.

### Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary:

- **Block Indices:**
  - Red block with circular cutout: Index 5
  - Yellow horizontal bar: Index 9 and Index 10
  - Green vertical block: Index 6
  - Orange triangular block: Index 14

### Assembly Order:

{
   Step1: Move block with index 5 (Red block with circular cutout)
   Step2: Move block with index 9 (Yellow horizontal bar)
   Step3: Move block with index 10 (Yellow horizontal bar)
   Step4: Move block with index 6 (Green vertical block)
   Step5: Move block with index 9 (Yellow horizontal bar)
   Step6: Move block with index 10 (Yellow horizontal bar)
   Step7: Move block with index 14 (Orange triangular block)
}
